			<ns0:name>bradc...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/110304265766688778552/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">&lt;b&gt;- Where are we today?&lt;/b&gt;
The Windows toolchain build is the slowest part of a full NaCl build, taking about four hours.

&lt;b&gt;- Why is this a problem?&lt;/b&gt;
It makes the tree stay red longer and slows everybody down.

&lt;b&gt;- The proposed enhancement:&lt;/b&gt;
Cleverness and effective optimizations are used to make the build faster. Perhaps we can get a faster machine or cache config results. Config is understood to be the slowest part of this.

&lt;b&gt;- Exit criteria:&lt;/b&gt;
Windows toolchain build takes about as long as the Linux and Mac builds.

&lt;b&gt;- Anticipated impact:&lt;/b&gt;
Developers don't spend as much time waiting for the Windows toolchain build.
